The '''2003â04 Syracuse Orangemen basketball team''' represented [[Syracuse University]] in NCAA men's basketball competition in the 2003â04 Division I season. The Head Coach was [[Jim Boeheim]], serving for his 28th year. The team played its home games at the [[Carrier Dome]] in [[Syracuse, New York|Syracuse]], [[New York]]. The team finished with a 23â8 (11â5) record, while making it to the Sweet 16 round of the [[2004 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|NCAA tournament]]. The team was led by junior [[Hakim Warrick]] and sophomore [[Gerry McNamara]]. Senior [[Jeremy McNeil]], juniors [[Craig Forth]] and [[Josh Pace]] and sophomore [[Billy Edelin]] were also major contributors.
This was the last season for Syracuse men's basketball under the Orangemen nickname. (At that time, women's teams and athletes were known as "Orangewomen".) Effective with the 2004â05 academic year, the school nickname became "Orange" for both men and women.
